01:33.960 --> 01:35.800
What are we doing?

01:35.830 --> 01:37.320
I work for you.

01:37.370 --> 01:40.400
I mean, this would be
complicated as hell.

01:40.440 --> 01:43.140
Yeah, you're right.
And as your employer,

01:43.180 --> 01:45.710
I cannot have you feel uncomfortable

01:45.740 --> 01:47.220
or pressured in any way.

01:47.240 --> 01:50.780
So... you're gonna have
to make a move on me.

01:53.920 --> 01:57.090
Do I look like a woman with moves?

01:57.120 --> 01:59.240
Just do what you feel is right.

01:59.320 --> 02:01.530
I am going to pretend to work

02:01.560 --> 02:04.500
and, uh, hope for the best.

02:13.360 --> 02:17.140
You've got a Fuji apple
sticker on your ass.

02:17.540 --> 02:20.750
I believe it's Golden Delicious.

02:24.960 --> 02:27.000
Can we just go back to work?

02:27.020 --> 02:28.520
This is getting too awkward.

02:28.560 --> 02:31.120
Yes, I agree.

02:31.260 --> 02:33.390
Um, can I borrow your stapler?

02:33.430 --> 02:35.120
Yes, sure.

02:42.440 --> 02:50.280
♪

02:52.540 --> 02:59.350
♪

03:00.900 --> 03:07.660
♪

03:09.140 --> 03:16.200
♪

03:19.060 --> 03:20.330
<i>"The Conners" is recorded</i>

03:20.340 --> 03:21.810
<i>in front of a live studio audience.</i>

03:21.840 --> 03:23.880
I'm done with my list!

03:23.980 --> 03:26.480
We made our Christmas lists
for you, Grandpa Dan.

03:26.570 --> 03:28.000
They're just suggestions.

03:28.030 --> 03:29.040
Don't get your hopes up.

03:29.050 --> 03:30.659
You're getting underwear
and a popcorn tin

03:30.660 --> 03:32.120
from the drug store.

03:33.860 --> 03:37.060
So, we're not getting anything we want?

03:37.080 --> 03:40.680
You really break my heart
when you put it like that.

03:40.710 --> 03:42.110
But no.

03:43.200 --> 03:45.680
But I really want a Plushy Pet backpack.

03:45.720 --> 03:46.980
It talks to you.

03:47.020 --> 03:48.380
But Mark talks to you.

03:48.420 --> 03:52.580
You don't want him to feel like
he's being replaced, do you?

03:52.680 --> 03:54.940
You know what won't make him feel bad?

03:55.020 --> 03:56.440
Crayons.

03:57.660 --> 03:59.030
Hi, guys.

03:59.060 --> 04:01.400
Grandpa wants to give me
crayons for Christmas.

04:01.430 --> 04:04.900
Well, we'll call Child Services
and let them sort it out.

04:06.620 --> 04:10.290
You know, Mary, most people
refer to them as Crayolas,

04:10.320 --> 04:11.800
but that's really a brand name,

04:11.820 --> 04:13.830
like Kleenex or cellophane.

04:13.860 --> 04:17.600
Crayola comes from the French
word <i>"craie,"</i> meaning "chalk,"

04:17.630 --> 04:20.380
and <i>"oleaginous," meaning "oily."</i>

04:22.100 --> 04:23.660
Can we go to school now?

04:23.720 --> 04:27.770
I see I've awakened the
educational curiosity in you.

04:28.060 --> 04:30.330
Oh, for God's sake, let 'em go.

04:32.110 --> 04:34.080
I'll help you pack 'em up, Deej.

04:34.110 --> 04:35.540
Dan, Peter wants to talk to you.

04:35.550 --> 04:37.540
He has a bike that needs restoring.

04:37.620 --> 04:40.250
Well, you've come to the right place.

04:40.290 --> 04:42.290
We do the same quality
work as the big guys,

04:42.320 --> 04:46.020
but cut a lot of corners and
pass the savings on to me.

04:55.270 --> 04:56.900
This isn't a bike.

04:56.940 --> 04:59.919
This is what you feed to other bikes.

04:59.920 --> 05:01.940
It's a classic Vespa.

05:01.980 --> 05:03.350
Did you ever see "Roman Holiday"

05:03.380 --> 05:05.159
with Audrey Hepburn and Gregory Peck?

05:05.160 --> 05:07.360
It's on my "After I Die" bucket list.

05:08.720 --> 05:10.720
I'm sorry. I don't fix foreign bikes.

05:10.750 --> 05:12.280
Ah, come on.

05:12.390 --> 05:14.139
I saw a bike like this in that movie,

05:14.140 --> 05:15.719
and I fell in love with it.

05:15.720 --> 05:17.920
The whole experience just made
me want to move to Italy.

05:17.980 --> 05:20.320
Well, you know, it's still there.

05:21.100 --> 05:22.260
So, Dan?

05:22.280 --> 05:23.620
What do you think of the Vespa?

05:23.960 --> 05:25.870
Well, like I told Audrey Hepburn here,

05:25.900 --> 05:28.320
I don't fix foreign bikes.

05:28.440 --> 05:30.510
Peter, could you get the
kids' Christmas presents

05:30.540 --> 05:33.300
- out of the trunk?
- I'll take Audrey or Katharine.

05:33.370 --> 05:35.780
You can't hurt me by
comparing me to a Hepburn.

05:38.810 --> 05:40.580
Come on.

05:40.620 --> 05:42.580
Dan, I bought it for Peter for Christmas

05:42.620 --> 05:44.026
because I knew you could restore it.

05:44.050 --> 05:45.590
You bought this for him?

05:45.620 --> 05:47.820
That's got to be at least three grand.

05:47.840 --> 05:49.096
You don't have that kind of money.

05:49.120 --> 05:51.520
I know it's a lot, but
we're both gonna enjoy it.

05:51.540 --> 05:52.690
Me sitting behind him,

05:52.730 --> 05:54.190
my cheek pressed against his back

05:54.230 --> 05:56.960
as we glide past the Trevi fountain.

05:57.000 --> 05:58.860
That's Rome. This is Lanford.

05:59.000 --> 06:00.630
We don't have fountains.

06:00.670 --> 06:03.140
We have a pipe that spills
sewage into the river.

06:04.740 --> 06:06.610
You're doing it for me, not for him.

06:06.640 --> 06:08.280
Definitely not doing it for him.

06:08.310 --> 06:09.856
You sure you're gonna be
riding on this thing?

06:09.880 --> 06:11.610
- Of course I am.
- Okay, then.

06:11.650 --> 06:13.750
I'll make sure the brakes work, too.

06:14.980 --> 06:17.720
♪

06:17.790 --> 06:21.620
So, how was work with hunky boss man?

06:21.660 --> 06:24.540
Um, we, you know, got along fine.

06:24.730 --> 06:26.130
Fine?

06:26.160 --> 06:29.060
That's your version of being overjoyed.

06:29.560 --> 06:31.540
You had sex with him.

06:32.670 --> 06:35.700
All I did was borrow his stapler,

06:35.740 --> 06:38.170
and then thank him.

06:38.180 --> 06:39.220
Twice on his desk.

06:42.080 --> 06:43.480
And how was it?

06:43.980 --> 06:46.280
Well, if you got to know, um...

06:46.320 --> 06:48.520
the sex was incredible.

06:48.720 --> 06:51.110
So you've only had sex with two guys,

06:51.120 --> 06:53.520
so you don't know good from bad.

06:53.560 --> 06:55.820
Let's just say it was average.

06:55.880 --> 06:57.830
Well, Ben must've liked it.

06:57.860 --> 06:59.830
He asked me over to his
apartment for dinner,

06:59.860 --> 07:01.960
and I can't wait to go.

07:02.030 --> 07:04.600
Oh, so it's gonna be a relationship.

07:04.630 --> 07:06.660
I smell disaster.

07:07.440 --> 07:09.170
Look, I know you're thinking that

07:09.210 --> 07:10.739
because I'm so spun out over Mom

07:10.740 --> 07:12.810
and divorcing David and money problems.

07:12.840 --> 07:14.840
You think I'm moving
faster than I should

07:14.880 --> 07:17.020
because I'm just looking
for a quick emotional fix.

07:17.080 --> 07:20.240
No, this isn't about you being
an emotional train wreck.

07:20.250 --> 07:21.520
That's too obvious.

07:22.820 --> 07:24.889
This is about your uncanny ability

07:24.890 --> 07:26.420
to pick the wrong guy for you.

07:26.560 --> 07:29.060
It's nice to be able to
share this with you.

07:29.090 --> 07:31.290
And you're completely wrong.

07:31.330 --> 07:33.360
Ben is finally the right guy.

07:33.400 --> 07:36.400
He's strong and confident,
and he knows what he wants.

07:36.430 --> 07:37.860
That's even worse.

07:38.770 --> 07:41.780
That's like two stubborn trains
heading towards each other

07:41.790 --> 07:42.800
on the same track.

07:42.810 --> 07:44.070
[IMITATES CRASH]

07:45.110 --> 07:47.280
You think I'm locked
into this little prison

07:47.310 --> 07:49.170
that I made for myself dating meek guys

07:49.180 --> 07:50.180
that I can push around, and

07:50.190 --> 07:51.440
it's not true... I've changed.

07:51.500 --> 07:52.520
Really?

07:52.560 --> 07:54.450
We shared a room for years.

07:54.580 --> 07:57.050
When you accused me of
having my Marky Mark poster

07:57.090 --> 08:00.720
on your side of the room, instead
of asking me to move it,

08:00.760 --> 08:02.590
you cut out Marky's eyes.

08:04.560 --> 08:08.030
I've just never seen you
this excited about a guy.

08:08.060 --> 08:09.579
I don't want you to fool yourself

08:09.580 --> 08:13.800
into thinking it's gonna be
all unicorns and rainbows.

08:13.840 --> 08:18.580
Be prepared for a rainstorm
and a horse head in the bed.

08:18.640 --> 08:21.810
Wow, most pregnant women are positive.

08:21.850 --> 08:23.700
That's gonna be one bitter little baby

08:23.720 --> 08:25.320
when it finally makes a break for it.

08:29.160 --> 08:30.860
♪

08:31.100 --> 08:32.570
Hey, Dan.

08:32.600 --> 08:34.330
Jackie said I could find you here.

08:34.370 --> 08:37.400
Yeah, I like it here.

08:37.440 --> 08:39.539
The food's bad, and
that keeps people away

08:39.570 --> 08:41.260
so I can drink in peace.

08:42.240 --> 08:44.010
I just wanted to pay you for the parts

08:44.039 --> 08:45.680
so that you could get started.

08:45.710 --> 08:46.860
Are you okay with a check?

08:46.980 --> 08:48.850
Sure. If it bounces,

08:48.880 --> 08:51.720
you're not gonna outrun me
on Barbie's Dream Scooter.

08:55.220 --> 08:59.260
Oh, you and Jackie have
an account together.

08:59.290 --> 09:00.400
When did this happen?

09:00.480 --> 09:01.839
Last week.

09:01.840 --> 09:03.170
We put my name on her account

09:03.180 --> 09:04.670
so that we could save money on fees

09:04.700 --> 09:06.920
by commingling our finances.

09:06.970 --> 09:08.700
No biggie.

09:09.140 --> 09:11.770
Commingling means two
people mingling money.

09:11.810 --> 09:13.820
Do you have anything to mingle?

09:13.910 --> 09:15.040
Not at the moment.

09:15.310 --> 09:17.880
I thought the master's
in Medieval Culture

09:17.900 --> 09:21.260
would've appealed to a
wider array of employers.

09:22.880 --> 09:24.489
But now I'm on the right track

09:24.490 --> 09:27.760
with Nordic history, music, and dance.

09:29.060 --> 09:31.330
Look, Jackie's a good person,

09:31.360 --> 09:33.660
and she's been single a long time,

09:33.700 --> 09:36.080
so her guard may not be up right now,

09:36.120 --> 09:38.230
but mine is.

09:38.270 --> 09:40.140
You're taking advantage
of my sister-in-law.

09:40.170 --> 09:41.339
No, I'm not.

09:41.340 --> 09:43.140
I'm gonna pay her back every penny,

09:43.170 --> 09:44.470
including tuition.

09:44.510 --> 09:46.080
She's paying your tuition?

09:46.200 --> 09:47.880
That's between me and Jackie.

09:47.910 --> 09:49.280
Just fix the bike.

09:49.310 --> 09:50.940
That's supposedly what you're good at.

09:51.850 --> 09:53.620
Excuse me?

09:53.650 --> 09:54.690
[SIGHS]

09:54.700 --> 09:57.150
Don't start a war of wits with me, Dan.

09:57.190 --> 09:58.860
You're unarmed.

10:00.900 --> 10:03.860
Touché. And since I am without wit,

10:03.890 --> 10:04.990
I'll take you out back

10:05.000 --> 10:07.660
and rub your face against the bricks.

10:07.700 --> 10:08.900
Mm, of course.

10:08.930 --> 10:11.460
The uneducated man resorts to violence.

10:11.500 --> 10:13.260
So predictable.

10:13.800 --> 10:15.570
Excuse me. Hold on.

10:15.610 --> 10:17.070
Don't leave without your check.

10:19.620 --> 10:20.680
Ow.

10:22.480 --> 10:24.380
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

10:27.250 --> 10:28.280
Hey.

10:28.320 --> 10:30.020
Right on time.

10:30.050 --> 10:31.640
You look beautiful.

10:31.720 --> 10:34.060
I already slept with you,
so let's just be cool.

10:34.090 --> 10:35.460
[LAUGHS]

10:38.230 --> 10:40.500
Oh, oh. I'm so sorry,

10:40.530 --> 10:43.930
but would you mind just
taking off your shoes?

10:43.970 --> 10:45.859
I, uh... I read this scientific thing

10:45.860 --> 10:47.176
about what you bring into your house

10:47.200 --> 10:48.219
on the bottom of your shoes,

10:48.220 --> 10:50.440
and it kind of freaked me out.

10:50.500 --> 10:52.660
Oh, yeah, did you not
know the ground was dirty

10:52.670 --> 10:53.679
before reading that?

10:53.680 --> 10:55.159
[LAUGHS]

10:55.160 --> 10:58.620
But, um, still just rather
not take my shoes off,

10:58.630 --> 11:00.940
makes me feel shorter.

11:00.950 --> 11:03.640
I'd rather you would.

11:04.560 --> 11:05.980
Okay.

11:07.990 --> 11:09.060
Oh.

11:09.090 --> 11:10.390
Oh, let's just...

11:12.360 --> 11:16.830
So, I am making vegan paella, huh?

11:17.070 --> 11:20.640
So if you would like to
open up a bottle of wine,

11:20.670 --> 11:23.000
anything red on the bottom
row should be fine.

11:23.410 --> 11:25.280
Oh, this white looks pretty good.

11:25.310 --> 11:30.250
Oh, uh, actually, red
usually stands up better

11:30.280 --> 11:32.460
to a tomato-sauce base.

11:32.520 --> 11:34.020
Any bottle on the bottom row there.

11:34.050 --> 11:35.800
You know, the red.

11:35.850 --> 11:39.560
Uh, if you hate it, then
we can open up a white.

11:39.960 --> 11:42.620
Yeah, I just tried it in
my mind, and I hated it.

11:42.630 --> 11:44.560
[CHUCKLES]

11:44.600 --> 11:46.800
Well, try it in a glass.

11:46.840 --> 11:48.770
You might like it.

11:48.800 --> 11:51.240
Uh, how about I just
help you with the food?

11:51.270 --> 11:52.360
Sure, that would be great.

11:52.370 --> 11:53.780
You can stir the paella.

11:59.040 --> 12:02.110
Hey, I'm glad you're here.

12:02.150 --> 12:03.310
Me, too.

12:09.050 --> 12:11.720
Huh?

12:11.760 --> 12:14.920
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

12:14.960 --> 12:18.230
It's better to add salt at the table.

12:18.260 --> 12:20.450
Well, let me just add a little,

12:20.460 --> 12:22.220
and you'll see that you like it.

12:23.280 --> 12:26.700
I tried it in my mind, and I hated it.

12:27.240 --> 12:30.440
You can't just grab something out
of my hand like I'm a child.

12:30.480 --> 12:31.980
I'm sorry.

12:32.210 --> 12:33.510
May I have the salt?

12:33.550 --> 12:35.600
- No.
- Please let go.

12:35.640 --> 12:37.460
- No, you let go.
- It's my salt.

12:37.480 --> 12:38.540
I'll buy you a new one.

12:38.550 --> 12:40.320
I asked you to stir, not season.

12:40.350 --> 12:41.760
I thought you're glad I'm here.

12:41.770 --> 12:44.520
I am. I'm just not
glad you're seasoning.

12:44.560 --> 12:46.520
Why are you fighting with me?

12:46.560 --> 12:47.830
I...

12:47.860 --> 12:50.030
Man, I spent hours
getting everything ready

12:50.060 --> 12:52.030
to show you a nice evening.

12:52.060 --> 12:54.870
Why can't you just
relax, enjoy yourself?

12:54.900 --> 12:57.270
Why can't you just let me enjoy myself

12:57.300 --> 12:59.370
the way I want to enjoy myself?

12:59.400 --> 13:01.740
Because the only way that
you can enjoy yourself

13:01.760 --> 13:04.480
is by making me not enjoy myself.

13:04.540 --> 13:07.450
Oh, well, I'm sorry I'm
ruining your evening.

13:07.460 --> 13:08.580
I'm getting my shoes.

13:08.610 --> 13:10.299
You can't wear them in here.

13:10.300 --> 13:11.650
I know.

13:12.260 --> 13:13.750
Well, where are you going?

13:13.790 --> 13:16.880
Home, to cook in my shoes
and salt everything.

13:19.620 --> 13:21.600
- Hi, there.
- Oh, hi.

13:21.640 --> 13:22.960
What are you doing here?

13:22.970 --> 13:24.470
I-I'm sorry. That sounded rude.

13:24.510 --> 13:26.640
Uh, what are you doing
here instead of David,

13:26.650 --> 13:28.740
who I wish was here instead of you?

13:28.760 --> 13:30.299
Well, he couldn't come,

13:30.300 --> 13:33.340
so I'll be going over the kids'
Christmas lists with you.

13:33.380 --> 13:35.720
I'll just wait for you at that table.

13:36.040 --> 13:37.450
Just throw something in a cup.

13:37.470 --> 13:38.740
I got to get out of here.

13:39.820 --> 13:41.540
The real reason I'm here

13:41.550 --> 13:44.510
is I'm having some problems with David.

13:44.540 --> 13:46.620
Mm.

13:46.630 --> 13:49.170
Well, look, I really don't
want to get involved,

13:49.200 --> 13:50.446
and I got to go back to the counter

13:50.470 --> 13:51.580
so someone doesn't grab my c...

13:51.600 --> 13:52.600
Oh.

13:52.640 --> 13:54.640
Thank you for doing something
you guys rarely do

13:54.670 --> 13:57.080
at the worst possible time.

13:57.220 --> 14:00.479
Okay, so, the problem with David

14:00.480 --> 14:02.380
is he's afraid to make decisions.

14:02.440 --> 14:04.280
It doesn't matter if
it's choosing a doctor

14:04.300 --> 14:06.100
or potato chips.

14:06.130 --> 14:07.870
How did you deal with that?

14:07.900 --> 14:09.370
I can't help you. I found the fact

14:09.400 --> 14:10.620
that he was born without a backbone

14:10.630 --> 14:12.259
one of his best features.

14:12.260 --> 14:13.860
[SCOFFS]

14:13.880 --> 14:16.600
I guess I'm just gonna have to
get him to see a therapist.

14:16.640 --> 14:18.039
Just don't over-fix him.

14:18.040 --> 14:19.856
There are guys that want
to make all the decisions,

14:19.880 --> 14:22.320
and that's way more annoying.

14:23.350 --> 14:25.120
You seem super tense.

14:27.760 --> 14:30.190
Uh, what ya doing there?

14:32.260 --> 14:34.900
I used to be a massage therapist.

14:34.930 --> 14:36.900
Are you dating a guy who's bossy?

14:36.930 --> 14:40.520
Uh, I-I really don't want to
talk about this with you.

14:40.540 --> 14:44.470
Sometimes saying it out
loud really helps.

14:44.510 --> 14:46.380
Just pretend like I'm not even here.

14:46.610 --> 14:49.280
Oh, I like that.

14:49.310 --> 14:51.510
